  "texts": [
    "The table presents results for tasks encompassing property prediction, yield prediction, and reagent selection across various datasets, such as BBBP (Blood-Brain Barrier Penetration), Tox21 (Toxicology in the 21st Century), and Suzuki-Coupling.",
    "Models include baseline methods like Random Forest (RF) and XGBoost, alongside GPT-4 and GPT-3.5 in zero-shot and random settings",
    "Goimailako Online Institutua, Udako Euskal Unibertsitatea (UEU, Summer Basque University), Donostia-San Sebastian, Spain",
    "Answer-only setting refers to prompting the model with the question by directly asking the correct answer."
